From 1f79c7e30a5eb33d3baff755cded5b4bc7209442 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tim Pietrusky <tim.pietrusky@runpod.io>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 23:06:36 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 02/19] turboquant(cuda): drop bulk-dequant temp buffers in v1
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The v1 LaunchTurboQuantAttention zeros the output anyway (the fp16 attention
delegation is gated behind v2), so allocating temp fp16 K/V buffers of size
B*H_kv*total_seq*head_size is pure waste — and OOMs at long context (LFM2.5
at 32K already crashed cudaMallocAsync on layer 2).

This commit calls DispatchEncodeDecode with total_seq_len=0 (which skips the
decode kernel entirely) and passes nullptrs for K_out/V_out. Encode still
runs and writes the cache; the rest is a memset of the output. Cuts the
v1 memory footprint by O(layers × B × H_kv × total_seq × head_size).

Verified on RTX A40 with the same calibration outputs:

