From 9440913c842de58173a63d131f0919587b231c05 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tim Pietrusky <tim.pietrusky@runpod.io>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 01:38:18 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 04/19] turboquant(cuda): make v2 work end-to-end on
 dynamic-cache GQA models (LFM2-1.2B)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The first v2 cut worked on Llama-3.2-1B because that model exports the past_kv
tensor with a fixed max_seq_len in dim[2]. HuggingFace transformers exports
(LFM2, etc.) use a *dynamic* past_kv shape — dim[2] = current past length —
which exposed five separate bugs in the TQ path. Fixed:

1. seqlen_present_kv_cache: was set to past_dims[2] (= past_len for dynamic
   exports, 0 at first prompt). That sized the present_kv output tensor to
   zero bytes and the encode kernel scribbled out of bounds. Now set to
   total_sequence_length.

2. cudaMemcpy of total_seq_lens_minus_one: the attn_mask subgraph produces
   this tensor on the same CUDA stream and its kernel may not have completed
   when we cudaMemcpy it host-side. Without a cudaStreamSynchronize the read
   races and returns garbage on multi-step decode. Now syncs before reading.

3. Past-content copy: the encode kernel only writes the new [past, total)
   slots, but the decode kernel reads all [0, total) slots. Past slots in the
   present buffer were uninitialized, so decode produced NaN/garbage K/V.
   Now cudaMemcpyAsync past_key/past_value into the first past_seq slots of
   present_key/present_value before encode.

4. fp16 saturation: large-magnitude K/V layers can produce vec_norm,
   v_scale, or v_zero values that don't fit in fp16 and saturate to ±inf
   when stored. The inf cascades through decode (60000 * 15 + 60000 = ~1M >
   fp16 max), produces NaN attention scores, and turns the entire model
   output into NaN on the next decode step. Now clamps all stored fp16
   values to ±60000 in encode and ±60000 in decode (V dequant) and in the
   output kernel.

5. norm_correction rsqrtf guard: when sum-of-squared-centroids is exactly 0
   (degenerate slot), rsqrtf returns +inf and the subsequent vec_norm * inf
   yields NaN. Now returns 0 for sum_sq < 1e-30.

LFM2-1.2B numbers (RTX A40, 6 GQA layers, head_dim=64, kbits=vbits=4,
norm_correction=on):

  prompt  fp16 decode/step   TQ-v2 decode/step   speedup
     64        6.4 ms             11.6 ms          0.55x
    256        6.5 ms              9.7 ms          0.67x
   1024       12.1 ms             11.1 ms          1.09x
   2048       18.0 ms             17.3 ms          1.04x
   4096       30.7 ms             17.0 ms          1.81x

Crossover is at ~1K context. The Llama-3.2-1B v2 numbers are unchanged.
