MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds TurboQuantKVFusion graph transformer that runs at session-create
time when the user sets session option
"optimization.turboquant_kv_method" to a TQ preset.  Effect: a stock
fp16 q4f16 .onnx file from HuggingFace becomes a TurboQuant model in
memory, with no disk-side conversion step and no duplicated weights.

What the transformer does (mirrors the offline python rewriter in
onnxruntime/python/tools/quantization/turboquant_kv/onnx_rewriter.py):

1. Iterates GroupQueryAttention nodes.  For each non-skipped layer:
   - Sets attributes kv_quant_method="turboquant", key_quant_bits,
     value_quant_bits, norm_correction.
   - Adds inputs at slots 14 (codebook) and 15 (hadamard) wired to
     shared graph initializers.
   - Rewrites past_key/past_value/present_key/present_value tensor
     types to uint8 with last-dim = max(K_slot, V_slot) bytes via
     NodeArg::UpdateTypeAndShape with override_types=true.
2. Lazy-creates the shared codebook (16 fp16 Lloyd-Max centroids) and
   Hadamard (NxN normalized Walsh-Hadamard) initializers once per
   (head_dim, key_bits) — naming is stable so re-runs reuse them.
3. Keeps MutableInputArgsCount in sync with the new input list size
   (sum == defs.size() invariant in ORT).
4. Honours boundary protection via session option
   "optimization.turboquant_kv_boundary" (default 2): leaves the first
   N and last N attention layers in fp16 for accuracy.

Lloyd-Max centroids and the Walsh-Hadamard matrix are computed in C++
at session-create time using the same fixed-point iteration as the
python reference; results match to within fp16 rounding noise.

Validation, vanilla LFM2-1.2B model_q4f16.onnx (NO offline rewrite),
prompt "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.":

  fp16 baseline argmax:  941 (' The')
  Option A TQ argmax:    941 (' The')   ✓ match
  cos sim of full logits: 0.98929
  top-10 token agreement: 9/10

User flow: download model from HuggingFace as-is, instantiate ORT
session with config_entry "optimization.turboquant_kv_method" =
"turboquant_4bit_nc", allocate past_kv inputs as uint8 with slot_bytes
shape on first call, reuse present_kv outputs for subsequent calls.
No python conversion script, no second .onnx file on disk.

Two new session option keys:
  optimization.turboquant_kv_method  ("turboquant_4bit_nc" etc.)
  optimization.turboquant_kv_boundary (int, default 2)
