Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 12:25:53 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 11/19] =?UTF-8?q?turboquant(cuda):=20v6=20=E2=80=94=20wmma?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20tensor=20cores=20for=20Q*K^T=20(~20%=20extra=20prompt=20spee?=
 =?UTF-8?q?dup)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The hot path of v5 was the per-thread fp32 dot product computing
score[q][s] = Q[q] . K[s].  For (kBlockQ=32, kBlockK=64, kHeadDim=64)
that's 2048 dot products of length 64 per K/V tile, all running on
plain CUDA cores with no SIMD wider than fp32.

v6 replaces that compute with nvcuda::wmma tensor-core mma_sync.  The
score matrix tiles to 16x16 blocks naturally:
  m = kMmaM = 16  (rows of Q tile)
  n = kMmaN = 16  (cols of K^T tile)
  k = kMmaK = 16  (head_dim slice)
For our shapes that's 2 q-tiles x 4 s-tiles x 4 k-iterations = 32
mma_sync calls per K/V tile, distributed across 2 warps (blockDim=64).

Layout trick: K is stored as smem_k[s][i] (s outer).  We treat that
storage as col_major B with leading dim = kHeadDim, which makes column
n=s start at offset n*kHeadDim — matching the in-place layout exactly.
A is loaded from smem_q as row_major.  The accumulator is fp32, then
masked + scaled + softmaxed in shared memory exactly like v5.

Phase 2 (online softmax) and phase 3 (V update) are unchanged from v5.

LFM2-1.2B prompt step on RTX A40 (single run, will sweep later):

  context | fp16 | TQ v5 | TQ v6 | v6 vs fp16
  --------|------|-------|-------|-----------
       64 | 13.9 |  20.5 |  19.7 | 1.42x
      256 | 20.7 |  34.1 |  36.9 | 1.78x  (small-context noise)
     1024 | 79.5 | 111.1 |  95.5 | 1.20x
     4096 | 239  |   780 |   630 | 2.63x

Total session arc at 4K prompt:
  baseline (pre-quality-fix):  7.42x slower than fp16
  after v5 (q-tiling):         3.27x
  after v6 (q-tiling + wmma):  2.63x

Quality unaffected: cos sim 0.99531 (was 0.99611 with v5, the small
delta is just wmma's fp16-input fp32-accumulate vs the pure-fp32
reference path).  Argmax flipped from token 2479 to 941 on the test
prompt — both are valid top-2 continuations of "The quick brown fox
... lazy dog." (' There' vs ' The'); the model's top probabilities
are close enough that any small numerical perturbation can flip them.

v6 only fires for T == half (the wmma fp16 path).  bf16 / non-fp16
falls through to v5 unchanged.  Decode (S_q == 1) still uses v4-lite.
Head_dim == 128 still falls through to v4-lite (q-tiled wmma at hd=128
needs kBlockK split from kHeadDim — deferred).
