This is the architectural fix we needed.  vLLM's TurboQuant prefill path
(turboquant_attn.py:542) doesn't read the quantized cache for the
first-chunk prefill — it runs vanilla FlashAttention on the raw fresh
fp16 K/V and quantizes asynchronously into the cache for FUTURE decode
steps.  Our v3..v7 was reinventing FA badly inside the TQ kernel.
Option ε does the same thing as vLLM:

- For first-prompt steps (past_seq == 0, S_q > 1) the orchestrator
  now calls onnxruntime::flash::mha_fwd_kvcache directly on the
  pre-rotated fp16 Q/K and raw fp16 V (already populated into
  d_K_fp16 / d_V_fp16 by LaunchCopyFreshKV in v7).  FA's "no internal
  append" mode is used: kcache/vcache are pre-populated, new_k/new_v
  passed as nullptr, seqlens_k = padded_seq_lens (= total_seq for
  first prompt), rotary disabled (we did it externally).
- The encode kernel still runs and writes the packed cache for
  FUTURE decode steps.  Decode steps (past_seq > 0) and short-q
  continuations still take the existing v7 / v6 path — that's where
  the smaller-cache bandwidth win actually pays off.

LFM2.5-1.2B-Instruct-ONNX, RTX A40, vanilla q4f16 model + Option A
graph rewrite + Option ε, median of 3 runs each:

  context | phase    | fp16  | TQ pre-ε | TQ ε   | TQ / fp16
  --------|----------|------:|---------:|-------:|----------
  4 K     | prompt   | 1160  | 1796     | 1127   | 0.97x  ✓ tie/win
  4 K     | decode   | 16.3  | 21.0     | 17.0   | 1.04x  ≈ tie
  32 K    | prompt   | 7241  | 18298    | 6741   | 0.93x  ✓ win
  32 K    | decode   | 93.6  | 80.0     | 87.0   | 0.93x  ✓ win

End-to-end at 32 K context, 200-token reply:
  fp16:  7241 + 200 * 94 = 26041 ms
  TQ:    6741 + 200 * 87 = 24141 ms   → TQ 7.3 % faster

Quality: cos sim vs fp16 = 1.00000 (FA on fresh fp16 K/V is
bit-equivalent to running fp16 baseline).  Argmax matches, top-10
identical.

This unblocks the long-context use case.  Decode steps still go
through our packed-cache path, so the 3.56x KV-cache memory saving
is preserved (not measured here but invariant from v7).

Mirrors the architectural decision in vLLM v0.20+:
  external/vllm/vllm/v1/attention/backends/turboquant_attn.py:542

The v6 wmma kernel and v5 q-tiled kernel still ship for the
short-continuation path (q_len > 1 with past_seq > 0) and for non-
fp16 inputs (bf16 falls through).  v8 (FA-2 multi-warp split-K on
packed cache) is no longer urgent — was needed only for the prompt
path which option ε now handles via stock FA.
