Subject: [PATCH 17/19] turboquant(cuda): tried cp.async double-buffered K/V
 load, regressed at our tile size. Reverted to plain vectorised uint4 loads.

cp.async pipelining adds cp.async.commit_group + cp.async.wait_group
bookkeeping per tile. At kBlockK=64 with hd=64, that's 2 sync points
per tile and only ~256 bytes worth of HBM hidden behind compute. The
per-tile sync overhead exceeded the overlap savings and the kernel
ran 28% slower (74 ms -> 95 ms decode at 32K).

Where this would help: bigger tiles (cp.async wins amortise as
load:compute ratio approaches 1) or v6 wmma's longer compute path.
Out of scope today; vectorised uint4 loads remain the shipping path.
