From b0ba97eff300571bfe651bf815d58d98996d5bd2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tim Pietrusky <tim.pietrusky@runpod.io>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 21:53:29 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 19/19] turboquant(webgpu): make Apple Silicon Metal path
 actually run
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Five fixes that take the WebGPU TurboQuant path from "compiles" to
"runs end-to-end on Apple Silicon Metal":

1. group_query_attention.cc: compute past_seq_len from past_key.shape[2]
   instead of seqlens_k input.  HF causal-LM benches commonly leave
   seqlens_k zero-filled on the prompt step; the past tensor's shape is
   the ground truth either way.  Mirrors what CheckInputs does for the
   fp16 path.

2. group_query_attention.cc: apply rotary inline before
   RunTurboQuantAttention.  ApplyFlashAttention's do_rotary path requires
   packed-QKV input which we don't have; do rotary up-front via the
   shared helper, then call the orchestrator with cos/sin = nullptr.

3. turboquant_attention.cc: alias uint8 packed cache as uint32 view
   tensors before binding to the decode shader.  ORT's
   ShaderVariableHelper rejects uint8 storage bindings (no WGSL type
   maps to a single u8); the WGSL templates already access the cache as
   `array<u32>`, so the fix is to construct uint32 alias tensors over
   the existing buffer.  Graph-level dtype stays uint8 — CUDA path is
   untouched.

4. turboquant_{encode,decode}.wgsl.template: drop `u` suffix from
   template-substituted compares.  `if (key_bits == 4u)` becomes
   `if (4 == 4u)` after substitution, which Tint rejects (AbstractInt
   vs u32 type mismatch).  Plain `4 == 4` typechecks.

5. turboquant_decode.wgsl.template: rename local variable `meta` →
   `v_meta_word`.  `meta` is reserved by WGSL.

6. turboquant_attention.h: mark TurboQuantEncodeProgram::norm_correction_
   `[[maybe_unused]]` so Mac clang -Werror=unused-private-field passes
   while encode is still placeholder.

End-to-end LFM2.5-1.2B benches on Apple Silicon Metal:

  ctx     fp16 decode   TQ decode    speedup
   4 K    37.4 ms/tok   18.1 ms/tok  2.07x
  16 K    88.9 ms/tok   65.1 ms/tok  1.37x
  32 K   348.7 ms/tok   94.3 ms/tok  3.70x

Prompt step is tied (Option-ε runs standard FA on fresh fp16 K/V).
